The Ministry of Justice have said it would be 'difficult or impossible' for Ched Evans to work abroad, meaning the convicted rapist may never play professional football again.

The 25-year-old is looking to return to football after being released from prison in October, but the striker's former club Sheffield United bowed to pressure on Thursday and withdrew their offer to allow Evans to train with them.

No other clubs in the Football League have expressed an interest in signing Evans, and the Ministry of Justice have confirmed it is unlikely the ex-Wales international can rebuild his career abroad.

