The PFA accepted the club's decision but added it hopes Evans will find a club.

'It may ultimately be of benefit to both parties to move on and for Ched to look for a fresh start at a different club,' a statement on Friday read.

'It is hoped that Ched will be given an opportunity at another club to return to the job he is trained to do.'

